The paper discusses a new hybrid consensus protocol for blockchain, which involves both Proof of Work (PoW) and Practical Byzantine Fault Tolerance (PBFT) verification. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cryptography (cs.CR), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and systems and control (cs.SY). However, given the focus on blockchain and consensus mechanisms, cs.CR and cs.DC are the most likely categories, followed by cs.DS, cs.NI, and cs.SY.
